TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: We will take the MAX value MIP since from front end users will have ability to only set the IND to 1 CANNOT make it back to 0. Whenever claim pass in to this mapplet, it can have multiple occurances from valid and invalid rule. MIP_IND = 1 is the expected value and 0 is default. So MAX will produce the correct result.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: MIP_IND

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: We will take the MIN value FULL_COINS since from front end users will have ability to only set the MIP IND to 1 CANNOT make it back to 0. Whenever claim pass in to this mapplet, it can have multiple occurances from valid and invalid rule. FULL_COINS =0 is the expected value when MIP is set . So MIN will produce the correct result.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: FULL_COINS_IND

TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION:
iif(OVRD_RULE_TYP_CD = 1, iif(not isnull(LCM_CUR_CD), IIF(RTRIM(LTRIM(LCM_CUR_CD)) = RTRIM(LTRIM(ORIG_LCM_CD_claim)), OVRD_RULE_NEW_VL, NULL), OVRD_RULE_NEW_VL) , NULL)

iif(OVRD_RULE_TYP_CD = 2, iif(not isnull(INCTV_TYP_CUR_CD), IIF(INCTV_TYP_CUR_CD = ORIG_INCTV_TYP_CD_claim, OVRD_RULE_NEW_VL, NULL), OVRD_RULE_NEW_VL) , NULL)

iif(OVRD_RULE_TYP_CD = 3, iif(not isnull(FRMLY_SRC_CUR_CD) and not isnull(FRMLY_CUR_ID), IIF(RTRIM(LTRIM(FRMLY_SRC_CUR_CD)) = RTRIM(LTRIM (ORIG_FRMLY_SRC_CD_claim)) AND RTRIM(LTRIM(FRMLY_CUR_ID)) = RTRIM(LTRIM(ORIG_FRMLY_ID_claim)) , substr(OVRD_RULE_NEW_VL, 1, 1), NULL), substr(OVRD_RULE_NEW_VL, 1, 1)) , null)
